In 30 days, the story of Jihe Hospital is highly condensed

Become a vivid profile of the fate of Wuhan City

The fate of Jihe Hospital in Wuhan diverged on January 23.

On New Year's Eve, the same day that Wuhan issued the "city closure" announcement, the non-public Medical Secondary General Hospital in Caidian District, Wuhan, was requisitioned as a designated treatment hospital for new pneumonia patients, one of fewer than 10 designated hospitals in Wuhan, it was then pushed to the forefront of a public health event that caught the world's attention.

Today, it is exactly one month from the closing of the city of Wuhan. For 30 days, the story of Jihe Hospital was highly condensed, a vivid profile of Wuhan's urban destiny.

Hub

The physician, Yan Fei, remembers the situation that night: More than 100 patients were brought to Jihe by ambulance one after another, quickly filling most of the 200 beds in the infected area, and the medical staff were running around exhausted in the newly renovated isolation ward. Critical equipment, such as suction machines and high-flow oxygen, was in considerable short supply, meeting the needs of only one ward; HIS Hospital Information System input failed to keep up, and doctors had to grab a pen and paper to quickly transcribe medical advice.

In the suddenly overloaded operation of the hospital, running a day of medical staff physical and mental exhaustion

At this point, the majority of the medical and nursing staff in the hospital has been on vacation, leaving only the remaining 50-odd medical and nursing staff. Protective Equipment was also stretched to the limit, with only 500 ordinary protective clothing in stock that did not meet the requirements of the area of separation and a serious shortage of high-grade medical masks above the N95 level. A doctor working 24 hours a day needs 1-2 protective clothing, night shift needs 2-3,500 protective clothing is only enough for more than 50 medical staff for 5 days.

The shortage of medical materials and medical professionals is a common situation in Wuhan and even Hubei Province on January 23. But jihe hospital is slightly different, it is a member of Fosun medical group, behind one of China's representative global enterprises -- Foshan fosun international (Fosun) .

At this time, Fosun's Shanghai headquarters, a large Hubei Chi aid plan in the simultaneous chess and advance.

The next day, at 9:46 a.m. on Jan. 24, Fosun's chairman, Guo Guangchang, launched the global health care allocation plan. Within 12 hours, 200,000 masks and 50,000 medical-grade suits had been located overseas. Global Partners and overseas business teams, the first generation of the system are all mobilized, orders are increasing, shipping channels are opening back home.

On January 24, Fosun global medical supplies deployment plan was launched, the global lock-up of large orders began

Since January 25, Fosun Medical Group has urgently mobilized its hospitals, from Jiangsu, Guangdong, Zhejiang, Anhui, Hunan and other places, to draw on the professional business backbone of suction, emergency treatment, critical care medicine, hospital sense, etc. , the fosun medical aid Hubei medical team was set up and arrived in Caidian District on the evening of February 6 as the first non-public Medical Aid Hubei medical team. So far, more than 30 members have been involved in Caidian District's first-line care efforts.

Fosun aid Hubei medical team assembled in Wuhan

Meanwhile, late on the night of January 28, the first batch of urgent medical supplies purchased by Fosun worldwide crossed 9,000 kilometers and arrived in Wuhan by plane and truck. As of midnight on February 22, Fosun had transported 1.01 million protective clothing, 1.24 million masks, 75,000 pairs of goggles and 110,000 pairs of medical gloves, totaling 2.435 million pieces of medical protective materials, plus 240 breathing machines. Most of them have been transported to the front line of Epidemic Prevention and control.

In the early morning of January 28, Fosun global deployment of the first batch of goods from Frankfurt to Shanghai, 29 early morning this batch of goods were rushed to the front line

Most of these materials are transported to Hubei Province, where they are collected at the Jihe Hospital, and then transported through this "hub" , point-to-point, to the prevention and control lines of 12 cities, including Xiaogan and Huanggang, including the Union Hospital, Tongji Hospital, south-central Hospital, Wuhan Central Hospital, Thor Mountain Hospital, Huoshenshan Hospital, including more than 80 hospitals.

Wuhan, a thoroughfare of nine provinces, was once the most convenient transit hub in China. When it pressed the pause button, pivots like the Jihe hospital spun spontaneously, developing a tenacious tenacity.

An ambulance that travels 1,000 kilometers a day

Piho never felt so important. The 42-year-old Wuhan native is the captain of the team at Jihe Hospital, driving the ambulance. Since January 24, the ambulance, which travels only to and from the area on weekdays, has regularly run more than 1,000 kilometers a day.

Piho drives a 120 to deliver supplies. "first aid is life. "

After the city was closed on Jan. 23, the Jihe Hospital immediately mobilized medical staff to return to work, but traffic in Wuhan was nearly paralyzed.

Most of the flights involved in Wuhan were cancelled, and several highways in the province were closed one by one within a day. The ambulance, which had a special pass, was put to great use.

In the first few days, he drove it to and from Xiaogan, Huanggang and Xiangyang, picking up six or seven paramedics a day. But before this, the hospital has issued the order, as long as is returning to work the medical staff, even if only one person, also must send a car to pick up.

At about the same time, Fosun Medical President Chen Yuqing, fosun medical chief executive Bao Qingui, and the head of the Respiratory Department of Xuzhou Mine General Hospital, Jia Xiaomin, set off on the first day of the Lunar New Year. They each made their way to Yueyang. An ambulance from Hang Seng Hospital in Shenzhen has been waiting in Yueyang. After the meeting, the three drove the ambulance full of N95 masks, protective clothing and other medical supplies to Wuhan.

Unbeknownst to them, the two ambulances will play a huge role in the future rescue operation throughout Hubei.

So far, only two days, to Chen Yuqing and Bao qingui-based Fosun Wuhan Forward Command in Jihe hospital has been operational.

"At that time, I didn't think I would have to undertake the deployment of urgently needed supplies for the Hubei Regional Hospital, " Chen recalled by telephone at 11 p.m, "We just want to be on the front line and protect our colleagues and encourage them to protect their patients. "

Chen Yuqing, general commander of Fosun Wuhan Front Line and President of Fosun medical group, carries medical supplies

This is already a difficult task. Jihe hospital is a second-level hospital, not to the smoking department, the hospital only about 260 medical staff. As a district-level fixed-point Treatment Hospital, it assumed the task of treating patients with mild or severe diseases.

Jihe hospital two Doctor Sun Mengbing, many people in isolation, the condition became worse, directly sent to here diagnosis and treatment. If you become critically ill, you must immediately be transferred to a higher hospital. In the three-level and hierarchical protection system of Wuhan, the designated hospitals like Jihe play the role of transit hub.

Among the more than 30,000 confirmed cases in Wuhan, patients with mild or severe diseases are a large sample group. Jia Xiaomin, an expert in the fight against SARS in 2003, was surprised by the number of patients in Jihe hospital -- as many as 200 beds, which has remained at full capacity since the first day of treatment. In the initial phase, Sun was responsible for 13 inpatients a day.

Jia Xiaomin remembers the panic he saw when he first came to the hospital. Most doctors don't come from the breathing profession, and surgeons, Orthopedic Surgeons, and even gynecologists get cold feet. Many of them do not have the knowledge of prevention and control, some shoes cover shallow, can not fully wrap the body; some wear a double-layer mask, "redundant, but also uncomfortable. ". The young nurse was short of breath, and at one point suspected she was infected, but it was just a lack of oxygen caused by wearing the mask for too long.

Under the twin pressures of panic and understaffing, they work for more than 10 hours a day in protective clothing at 25 degrees. Goggles stuck in the face, a take off, showing deep ligature marks.

Can the paramedics keep up? Can Medical supplies keep up? Questions are being asked all over Wuhan.

The lettering on those suits is crooked

Wuhan Jihe Hospital medical staff back

Piho won't forget the late night of January 28th. At the intersection of Wuhan and Caidian District Highway, he and Bao Qiangui were going to pick up the first medical supplies from Fosun to the front line from Shanghai.

On the evening of January 26, Fosun mobilized global forces to procure 10,000 masks to arrive in Shanghai. After more than 20 hours, they will be transported to the front through the Shanghai-wuhan 900 km freight lifeline. And every day after that, it will never stop.

It was a windy and rainy night and the temperature was just over zero degrees. The rain made a jarring noise against the car window. According to the requirements of the two ambulances parked at the monitoring station, on foot rushed to the service area waiting for two Shanghai plates, up to 17.5 meters long red box-type truck.

The first car missed the intersection, Pihao quickly drove, chasing dozens of kilometers back.

It was freezing rain and the roads were closed. "Like Wuhan's air is full of viruses" , Pihao flashed out the idea.

Then he saw Baoqingui in the rain with a cell phone call for an hour, to guide the car over, but also to communicate the driver's protection. At about 2 am, the two containers were finally unloaded at the Jihe Hospital. The truck was disinfected and immediately returned to Shanghai.

Jihe hospital is divided into two areas. Zone 1-3 is in the "clean" West Wing, and zone 4-8 is in the "polluted" East Wing, which is also the isolation ward for new pneumonia patients. Boxes of materials were moved into the West floor warehouse, because storage space is not enough, many piled up in the outpatient hall.

At 5 pm on January 31, Wu Qiong, the 40-year-old director of the Sensory Department of Yueyang's Guangji Hospital, arrived at the hospital and happened to see Fosun's supply vehicles parked in front of the hospital. A warm current rushed up from his stomach. "It's just a feeling of peace, " he said, grinning. The main responsibility of hospital sense department is to prevent cross infection of patients and medical staff.

Tao Fei, the ICU expert of Foshan Chancheng Central Hospital, went to Jihe hospital first thing is to investigate the material building. He was born in the Department of critical care most concerned about high-flow oxygen therapy equipment, which is the treatment of severe new coronary pneumonia patients indicator equipment, hospital in the province many urgent. When told that there are 20 sets, Shanghai procurement over, just in place, "immediately know the bottom of my heart. ".

Foshan Zen medicine ICU director Tao Fei (second right) and the medical team of two other experts for patient consultation

Abundance can sometimes be a "sweet" burden. Tao Fei received every day are the highest standard of protective clothing, and not the same style, some pants edge with the Zodiac, some underworld or red road. He knew English, Japanese, French, and some of the letters on the labels were too crooked to read.

The difference is that some zippers are so high that they can get stuck up to the neck; others require self adhesive to seal in between Zippers; and still others are so airtight that they cover the entire face, exposing only the eyes. "There's a hat and a mask under the suit. It's like wearing three layers of clothing on a hot day. "

He later asked to know that this is Fosun in the first time from more than 20 countries in the world's rapid procurement of medical-grade protective clothing. The squiggly letters could be Hindi or Portuguese, corresponding to where they were purchased.

The protective clothing that arrived at the relief and hospital in different countries read: Fosun Global Material Distribution

Three of my patients have been discharged

Fosun medical elite to join, the core goal of only one: through early treatment, so that patients do not develop serious illness. New Coronaviruses are tricky because they can cause the disease to suddenly deteriorate after a period of relative stability, "holding the nodes is crucial, " Tao explained.

Targeted training is necessary. Jia Xiaomin arrived in the first few days of the hospital, the main focus is to let the hospital to fill the smoking section of the basic knowledge as quickly as possible. Every night, he dissected the methods of diagnosing and treating new coronary pneumonia one by one from respiratory infection, the basic manifestations of pneumonia, how to identify on the image, how to check blood items, how to do blood item analysis, etc. , defining oxygen partial pressure and oxygen saturation is a key concern for most of the medical staff drawn from other departments to have a focus.

Tao Fei in the treatment of patients, the most important work is to comb the case, the development of critical patients in the hospital history. ICU has a famous saying: There is no sudden change of illness, only the change of illness was suddenly found. Whether to find the symptom of disease in time or not determines whether a fresh life will turn to serious disease or go home for Reunion, which is also the value of Jihe hospital as a diagnosis and treatment hub.

Fosun Medical anti-epidemic Expert Group leader Professor Jia Xiaomin in rounds, and encourage patients

Yang Yong, a medical team leader from Shenzhen's Hang Seng Hospital in Wuhan, had a typical case. On the first day, the patient's sats were normal. By the time of rounds the next day, his fingers were all purple, and only 80 percent of them were Oxygenation, a red flag. After treatment with a high-flow oxygen machine, the patient improved.

"every point in the progression from early stage to critical illness must be controlled, " says Tao, explaining that the Oxygenation data is one of the points at which timely oxygen therapy can reduce a patient's chance of developing a critical illness. The mortality rate of severe cases is very high. As of February 15, there were 8,530 severe cases in Wuhan, with a case fatality rate of 2.96% , which is higher than that in Hubei and the whole country.

One of the patients in his ward got better after oxygen therapy. But the airflow through the nasal cavity, bring bad proprioception. "The patient is repeated repeatedly, do not cooperate, transfer to superior hospital to intubate finally. " Tao Fei both deplore and unwilling.

How to get the patients to cooperate, how to comfort the patients, this is also a big problem for the hospital.

It's normal for patients to be anxious when they're in isolation. One patient was admitted because of abdominal pain and nucleic acid test positive. He has been emotional, do not understand how the stomach pain received here in the hospital, suspected a misdiagnosis, asked again nucleic acid testing, also do not cooperate with treatment, every day just repeated the test results. The medical staff had to patiently explain the clinical manifestations of the new coronary pneumonia and persuade him to treat it with peace of mind. Three days later, he saw the word "positive" in his face lost, after a long silence, said a "Go! Wuhan Go! China go! "

Ji He hospital's head nurse Wu Jiao summed up the experience, as a medical staff, first of all to actively disseminate knowledge to patients, as far as possible to eliminate their inner fear, just said "don't be afraid" of the word useless.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital head nurse Wu Jiao in the isolation ward

And one of the patients told her she was in the hospital with her family around. Now this illness, the family can not accompany, can only regard the nurse as the family member. "We talk to them, they will feel very relieved, feel much better, more willing to treat" , Wu Jiao introduced his method.

Patient Comfort is also a manpower challenge. Since the day of the "city closure" , the four head nurses of Jihe Hospital have worked 29 days in a row, refusing to get off the line of fire.

Wu Jiao, from the rehabilitation department, was transferred to the infected area for the first time. "The workload has multiplied. ". Because many patients have difficulty breathing, she spends a lot of time with instruments other than intravenous fluids and other routine work. Breathing Machine, nebulizer, central oxygen supply system, high-flow hygroscopic therapeutic apparatus, etc, are in uninterrupted use, must ensure the stability of the patient's vital signs.

Compared with common pneumonia, new coronary pneumonia is highly infectious, which requires special attention to prevent cross-infection in the ward. The nurses work every day, spraying disinfectant, every other day to the patient to change the bed linen cover, unified to the designated place cleaning and disinfection. These jobs used to be shared by caregivers, but many of them were cut off by traffic and now have to be handled by health care workers themselves.

The arrival of medical professionals like Tao Fei and Wu Qiong has greatly relieved the pressure on the hospital itself. The hospital staff would joke that seeing people arrive was like seeing a cookie.

When Wu Qiong, director of the Hospital Sense Department of Yueyang Guangji Hospital, heard that she needed to go to Wuhan for support, she readily agreed

We're getting more men. A few days ago, the head of the Jihe Hospital, Liu Zaikui, asked the hospital to force shifts, requiring medical staff to take shifts. At present, the ratio of medical care / patient is about 1:3 in Jihe hospital, with about 36 patients in one ward and 12 doctors and nurses on shift, the treatment is gradually entering the normal stage.

The patient also slowly steady state of mind, more understanding of the medical staff is not easy. For example, when you're talking to a doctor, you keep your distance. When you cough, do not approach. Many initially impatient patients, learned that the aid team is from Jiangsu, Guangdong's specialist elite, they raised their fists high, to make encouraging gestures.

Medics are no longer in high spirits, scribbling the names of each other's protective suits, occasionally drawing a heart and adding one-liners such as "I want to go back to Chongqing for hot pot" .

Yan said none of the patients in his ward had died and three had been discharged. "That's what keeps the front line going. "

Yan Fei, a physician at Jihe Hospital in Wuhan, China, checks the CT results of a patient

Each mask "human flesh" express delivery to more than 80 hospitals

12 days ago, Piho's ambulance broke down. On the way back from the airport to the hospital, the clutch of the ambulance full of medical protective equipment burned out.

From January 29, the first batch of Fosun procurement materials arrived in Wuhan, Chen Yuqing and Bao Qingui one of the focus of work is to solve the problem of effective distribution of materials in Hubei Province.

Every day, the two receive hundreds of phone calls and thousands of wechat messages from Epidemic Prevention Headquarters at all levels, major hospitals, provincial medical teams in Hubei Province, and even hospital department directors, all hoping for emergency assistance with protective materials.

No one thought, Wuhan and Hubei's medical supplies shortage, is a continuing problem. On January 31, the eighth day of the closure, the Government of the People's Republic of China held a press conference, specifically responding to the question, "the Red Cross has received a large number of materials, why are hospitals still short of materials? " .

Put the life-saving medical protection materials to the sun can not reach, the government temporarily out of place, can only point-to-point "human meat" express delivery. The car has to be used frequently because emergency is life-saving.

But with so much demand, how can supplies be efficiently distributed? Command has established that waste is an inefficient donation, that every mask must be used to its best advantage, and that every life-threatening item must be delivered precisely.

On behalf of Fosun and Jihe Hospital, 1000 sets of medical-grade protective clothing were delivered to the Wuhan Union Hospital (Wuhan Union Hospital) by Bao Qingui, Fosun's vice-commander in Wuhan and CEO of Fosun Medical

Chen Yuqing and baoqingui adopted the most earthy method -- a telephone call. Each day, the two spent more than 14 hours staring at their phones, keeping in close contact with people on the ground, verifying the true status of each hospital, and tracking their changing roles during the war.

Hard data are how many quarantined wards are set up in a hospital, and how many health care workers work in quarantined wards and fever clinics. If a hospital does not have an isolation ward, but only a fever clinic, then medical-grade protective clothing with sealant tape and N95 masks in the red zone are not covered.

Of course, we must also analyze the situation in the affected areas. The situation in Xiaogan and Huanggang is the most serious among the prefectural-level cities under Hubei's jurisdiction because they are close to Wuhan and their medical resources are not particularly abundant. Xiangyang, Yichang and Jingzhou are among the worst-hit areas, with at least a few large triple-a hospitals.

From the other side in the communication attitude, can also judge the degree of shortage of protective materials. "For example, if it's really urgent, he will pick it up as soon as I call him. If I say I'll get a car in two days, it means I'm not so nervous at the moment, " Bao said, analyzing the verbal message.

A few days ago, in order to study the specific needs of the prefectural-level cities around Wuhan, the two of them pulled up at least a direct-line docking group of the epidemic prevention headquarters of nine prefectural-level cities, including Xiaogan, Huanggang, Xiangyang, Shiyan and Jingmen, contact various channels —— colleagues, classmates, friends, places, and dynamics.

"because there are urgent appeals for help everywhere, demand can not be evenly distributed, and it is very likely that it will be misplaced, " Chen said. Therefore, which hospital shoes instead of goggles, which city is short of diapers instead of protective clothing, must not include the end, "are important resources to save lives, must not be mismatched, easy waste. "

Jihe hospital as a transfer station of the special status of the hub gradually emerged. Every day, a truck from Shanghai will come to the rapid unloading of goods, the hospital, two ambulances, two commercial vehicles will inventory the finished goods, a trip to distribute.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital

"daily average 1000 kilometers, at least seven or eight times, more than a dozen times, how can not run bad? " Pihao also in heartache that drove seven or eight years of ambulance. Three days ago, he and Chen Yuqing, Bao qingui respectively drove cars set out, Wuhan Jihe Hospital as the pivot point, back to Xiaogan, Huanggang and Jingzhou, a total of six times. He left at 8:30 a.m. and eventually returned to the hospital the next morning. "The ambulance has limited space and can only carry 1.5 tons of supplies at a time, and can only go back and forth. "

On the evening of January 31, Bao Qingui donated 1,000 sets of medical grade protective clothing to the Wuhan Union Hospital on behalf of Fosun. Since then, Chen Yuqing and Bao qingui have distributed nearly 400,000 sets of medical protective materials over 20 days, covering more than 80 hospitals in 12 cities throughout Hubei Province.

At the scene of the donation at Thor Mountain Hospital, the ambulance driver, Pi Hao, described a "spectacular" scene: The area was brightly lit for several kilometers, with public security, armed police, military, city management, Road Administration and other institutions, trucks, trucks, duty vehicles, ambulances, construction vehicles and other vehicles, meet here; people in different uniforms division of labor cooperation, we are very busy, too busy, like a screw to high-speed operation.

On the evening of February 11, Fosun transported 5,000 rubber protective clothing, 10,000 red zone masks, 30 non-invasive suction machines and 1 negative pressure ambulance, which had been urgently procured from the whole world, to the Wuhan Thunder Mountain Hospital. In the face of the epidemic, a handshake ceremony is replaced by a bow

The power of the state is in action, bringing unlimited confidence and confidence. However, a private enterprise to a non-public medical hospital as a Fulcrum, but also in front of the efforts to make up for the job, do a heart and responsibility.

Baoqingui arrived in Wuhan with a 24-inch suitcase containing only two down jackets. One for delivery, one for carrying, and one for cleaning. His garment, dubbed by Fosun as a "black gold suit" , has become a bit stiff after nearly a month of drinking and Sun and rain.

"Let's just hang out like this, " he said, adding that the epidemic would not end.

When the flowers bloom, the soldiers return

On the evening of January 26, Fosun mobilized global forces to procure 10,000 masks to arrive in Shanghai. After more than 20 hours, they will be transported to the front through the Shanghai-wuhan 900 km freight lifeline. And every day after that, it will never stop.

It was a windy and rainy night and the temperature was just over zero degrees. The rain made a jarring noise against the car window. According to the requirements of the two ambulances parked at the monitoring station, on foot rushed to the service area waiting for two Shanghai plates, up to 17.5 meters long red box-type truck.

The first car missed the intersection, Pihao quickly drove, chasing dozens of kilometers back.

It was freezing rain and the roads were closed. "Like Wuhan's air is full of viruses" , Pihao flashed out the idea.

Then he saw Baoqingui in the rain with a cell phone call for an hour, to guide the car over, but also to communicate the driver's protection. At about 2 am, the two containers were finally unloaded at the Jihe Hospital. The truck was disinfected and immediately returned to Shanghai.

Jihe hospital is divided into two areas. Zone 1-3 is in the "clean" West Wing, and zone 4-8 is in the "polluted" East Wing, which is also the isolation ward for new pneumonia patients. Boxes of materials were moved into the West floor warehouse, because storage space is not enough, many piled up in the outpatient hall.

At 5 pm on January 31, Wu Qiong, the 40-year-old director of the Sensory Department of Yueyang's Guangji Hospital, arrived at the hospital and happened to see Fosun's supply vehicles parked in front of the hospital. A warm current rushed up from his stomach. "It's just a feeling of peace, " he said, grinning. The main responsibility of hospital sense department is to prevent cross infection of patients and medical staff.

Tao Fei, the ICU expert of Foshan Chancheng Central Hospital, went to Jihe hospital first thing is to investigate the material building. He was born in the Department of critical care most concerned about high-flow oxygen therapy equipment, which is the treatment of severe new coronary pneumonia patients indicator equipment, hospital in the province many urgent. When told that there are 20 sets, Shanghai procurement over, just in place, "immediately know the bottom of my heart. ".

Foshan Zen medicine ICU director Tao Fei (second right) and the medical team of two other experts for patient consultation

Abundance can sometimes be a "sweet" burden. Tao Fei received every day are the highest standard of protective clothing, and not the same style, some pants edge with the Zodiac, some underworld or red road. He knew English, Japanese, French, and some of the letters on the labels were too crooked to read.

The difference is that some zippers are so high that they can get stuck up to the neck; others require self adhesive to seal in between Zippers; and still others are so airtight that they cover the entire face, exposing only the eyes. "There's a hat and a mask under the suit. It's like wearing three layers of clothing on a hot day. "

He later asked to know that this is Fosun in the first time from more than 20 countries in the world's rapid procurement of medical-grade protective clothing. The squiggly letters could be Hindi or Portuguese, corresponding to where they were purchased.

The protective clothing that arrived at the relief and hospital in different countries read: Fosun Global Material Distribution

Three of my patients have been discharged

Fosun medical elite to join, the core goal of only one: through early treatment, so that patients do not develop serious illness. New Coronaviruses are tricky because they can cause the disease to suddenly deteriorate after a period of relative stability, "holding the nodes is crucial, " Tao explained.

Targeted training is necessary. Jia Xiaomin arrived in the first few days of the hospital, the main focus is to let the hospital to fill the smoking section of the basic knowledge as quickly as possible. Every night, he dissected the methods of diagnosing and treating new coronary pneumonia one by one from respiratory infection, the basic manifestations of pneumonia, how to identify on the image, how to check blood items, how to do blood item analysis, etc. , defining oxygen partial pressure and oxygen saturation is a key concern for most of the medical staff drawn from other departments to have a focus.

Tao Fei in the treatment of patients, the most important work is to comb the case, the development of critical patients in the hospital history. ICU has a famous saying: There is no sudden change of illness, only the change of illness was suddenly found. Whether to find the symptom of disease in time or not determines whether a fresh life will turn to serious disease or go home for Reunion, which is also the value of Jihe hospital as a diagnosis and treatment hub.

Fosun Medical anti-epidemic Expert Group leader Professor Jia Xiaomin in rounds, and encourage patients

Yang Yong, a medical team leader from Shenzhen's Hang Seng Hospital in Wuhan, had a typical case. On the first day, the patient's sats were normal. By the time of rounds the next day, his fingers were all purple, and only 80 percent of them were Oxygenation, a red flag. After treatment with a high-flow oxygen machine, the patient improved.

"every point in the progression from early stage to critical illness must be controlled, " says Tao, explaining that the Oxygenation data is one of the points at which timely oxygen therapy can reduce a patient's chance of developing a critical illness. The mortality rate of severe cases is very high. As of February 15, there were 8,530 severe cases in Wuhan, with a case fatality rate of 2.96% , which is higher than that in Hubei and the whole country.

One of the patients in his ward got better after oxygen therapy. But the airflow through the nasal cavity, bring bad proprioception. "The patient is repeated repeatedly, do not cooperate, transfer to superior hospital to intubate finally. " Tao Fei both deplore and unwilling.

How to get the patients to cooperate, how to comfort the patients, this is also a big problem for the hospital.

It's normal for patients to be anxious when they're in isolation. One patient was admitted because of abdominal pain and nucleic acid test positive. He has been emotional, do not understand how the stomach pain received here in the hospital, suspected a misdiagnosis, asked again nucleic acid testing, also do not cooperate with treatment, every day just repeated the test results. The medical staff had to patiently explain the clinical manifestations of the new coronary pneumonia and persuade him to treat it with peace of mind. Three days later, he saw the word "positive" in his face lost, after a long silence, said a "Go! Wuhan Go! China go! "

Ji He hospital's head nurse Wu Jiao summed up the experience, as a medical staff, first of all to actively disseminate knowledge to patients, as far as possible to eliminate their inner fear, just said "don't be afraid" of the word useless.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital head nurse Wu Jiao in the isolation ward

And one of the patients told her she was in the hospital with her family around. Now this illness, the family can not accompany, can only regard the nurse as the family member. "We talk to them, they will feel very relieved, feel much better, more willing to treat" , Wu Jiao introduced his method.

Patient Comfort is also a manpower challenge. Since the day of the "city closure" , the four head nurses of Jihe Hospital have worked 29 days in a row, refusing to get off the line of fire.

Wu Jiao, from the rehabilitation department, was transferred to the infected area for the first time. "The workload has multiplied. ". Because many patients have difficulty breathing, she spends a lot of time with instruments other than intravenous fluids and other routine work. Breathing Machine, nebulizer, central oxygen supply system, high-flow hygroscopic therapeutic apparatus, etc, are in uninterrupted use, must ensure the stability of the patient's vital signs.

Compared with common pneumonia, new coronary pneumonia is highly infectious, which requires special attention to prevent cross-infection in the ward. The nurses work every day, spraying disinfectant, every other day to the patient to change the bed linen cover, unified to the designated place cleaning and disinfection. These jobs used to be shared by caregivers, but many of them were cut off by traffic and now have to be handled by health care workers themselves.

The arrival of medical professionals like Tao Fei and Wu Qiong has greatly relieved the pressure on the hospital itself. The hospital staff would joke that seeing people arrive was like seeing a cookie.

When Wu Qiong, director of the Hospital Sense Department of Yueyang Guangji Hospital, heard that she needed to go to Wuhan for support, she readily agreed

We're getting more men. A few days ago, the head of the Jihe Hospital, Liu Zaikui, asked the hospital to force shifts, requiring medical staff to take shifts. At present, the ratio of medical care / patient is about 1:3 in Jihe hospital, with about 36 patients in one ward and 12 doctors and nurses on shift, the treatment is gradually entering the normal stage.

The patient also slowly steady state of mind, more understanding of the medical staff is not easy. For example, when you're talking to a doctor, you keep your distance. When you cough, do not approach. Many initially impatient patients, learned that the aid team is from Jiangsu, Guangdong's specialist elite, they raised their fists high, to make encouraging gestures.

Medics are no longer in high spirits, scribbling the names of each other's protective suits, occasionally drawing a heart and adding one-liners such as "I want to go back to Chongqing for hot pot" .

Yan said none of the patients in his ward had died and three had been discharged. "That's what keeps the front line going. "

Yan Fei, a physician at Jihe Hospital in Wuhan, China, checks the CT results of a patient

Each mask "human flesh" express delivery to more than 80 hospitals

12 days ago, Piho's ambulance broke down. On the way back from the airport to the hospital, the clutch of the ambulance full of medical protective equipment burned out.

From January 29, the first batch of Fosun procurement materials arrived in Wuhan, Chen Yuqing and Bao Qingui one of the focus of work is to solve the problem of effective distribution of materials in Hubei Province.

Every day, the two receive hundreds of phone calls and thousands of wechat messages from Epidemic Prevention Headquarters at all levels, major hospitals, provincial medical teams in Hubei Province, and even hospital department directors, all hoping for emergency assistance with protective materials.

No one thought, Wuhan and Hubei's medical supplies shortage, is a continuing problem. On January 31, the eighth day of the closure, the Government of the People's Republic of China held a press conference, specifically responding to the question, "the Red Cross has received a large number of materials, why are hospitals still short of materials? " .

Put the life-saving medical protection materials to the sun can not reach, the government temporarily out of place, can only point-to-point "human meat" express delivery. The car has to be used frequently because emergency is life-saving.

But with so much demand, how can supplies be efficiently distributed? Command has established that waste is an inefficient donation, that every mask must be used to its best advantage, and that every life-threatening item must be delivered precisely.

On behalf of Fosun and Jihe Hospital, 1000 sets of medical-grade protective clothing were delivered to the Wuhan Union Hospital (Wuhan Union Hospital) by Bao Qingui, Fosun's vice-commander in Wuhan and CEO of Fosun Medical

Chen Yuqing and baoqingui adopted the most earthy method -- a telephone call. Each day, the two spent more than 14 hours staring at their phones, keeping in close contact with people on the ground, verifying the true status of each hospital, and tracking their changing roles during the war.

Hard data are how many quarantined wards are set up in a hospital, and how many health care workers work in quarantined wards and fever clinics. If a hospital does not have an isolation ward, but only a fever clinic, then medical-grade protective clothing with sealant tape and N95 masks in the red zone are not covered.

Of course, we must also analyze the situation in the affected areas. The situation in Xiaogan and Huanggang is the most serious among the prefectural-level cities under Hubei's jurisdiction because they are close to Wuhan and their medical resources are not particularly abundant. Xiangyang, Yichang and Jingzhou are among the worst-hit areas, with at least a few large triple-a hospitals.

From the other side in the communication attitude, can also judge the degree of shortage of protective materials. "For example, if it's really urgent, he will pick it up as soon as I call him. If I say I'll get a car in two days, it means I'm not so nervous at the moment, " Bao said, analyzing the verbal message.

A few days ago, in order to study the specific needs of the prefectural-level cities around Wuhan, the two of them pulled up at least a direct-line docking group of the epidemic prevention headquarters of nine prefectural-level cities, including Xiaogan, Huanggang, Xiangyang, Shiyan and Jingmen, contact various channels —— colleagues, classmates, friends, places, and dynamics.

"because there are urgent appeals for help everywhere, demand can not be evenly distributed, and it is very likely that it will be misplaced, " Chen said. Therefore, which hospital shoes instead of goggles, which city is short of diapers instead of protective clothing, must not include the end, "are important resources to save lives, must not be mismatched, easy waste. "

Jihe hospital as a transfer station of the special status of the hub gradually emerged. Every day, a truck from Shanghai will come to the rapid unloading of goods, the hospital, two ambulances, two commercial vehicles will inventory the finished goods, a trip to distribute.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital

"daily average 1000 kilometers, at least seven or eight times, more than a dozen times, how can not run bad? " Pihao also in heartache that drove seven or eight years of ambulance. Three days ago, he and Chen Yuqing, Bao qingui respectively drove cars set out, Wuhan Jihe Hospital as the pivot point, back to Xiaogan, Huanggang and Jingzhou, a total of six times. He left at 8:30 a.m. and eventually returned to the hospital the next morning. "The ambulance has limited space and can only carry 1.5 tons of supplies at a time, and can only go back and forth. "

On the evening of January 31, Bao Qingui donated 1,000 sets of medical grade protective clothing to the Wuhan Union Hospital on behalf of Fosun. Since then, Chen Yuqing and Bao qingui have distributed nearly 400,000 sets of medical protective materials over 20 days, covering more than 80 hospitals in 12 cities throughout Hubei Province.

At the scene of the donation at Thor Mountain Hospital, the ambulance driver, Pi Hao, described a "spectacular" scene: The area was brightly lit for several kilometers, with public security, armed police, military, city management, Road Administration and other institutions, trucks, trucks, duty vehicles, ambulances, construction vehicles and other vehicles, meet here; people in different uniforms division of labor cooperation, we are very busy, too busy, like a screw to high-speed operation.

On the evening of February 11, Fosun transported 5,000 rubber protective clothing, 10,000 red zone masks, 30 non-invasive suction machines and 1 negative pressure ambulance, which had been urgently procured from the whole world, to the Wuhan Thunder Mountain Hospital. In the face of the epidemic, a handshake ceremony is replaced by a bow

The power of the state is in action, bringing unlimited confidence and confidence. However, a private enterprise to a non-public medical hospital as a Fulcrum, but also in front of the efforts to make up for the job, do a heart and responsibility.

Baoqingui arrived in Wuhan with a 24-inch suitcase containing only two down jackets. One for delivery, one for carrying, and one for cleaning. His garment, dubbed by Fosun as a "black gold suit" , has become a bit stiff after nearly a month of drinking and Sun and rain.

"Let's just hang out like this, " he said, adding that the epidemic would not end.

Under the twin pressures of panic and understaffing, they work for more than 10 hours a day in protective clothing at 25 degrees. Goggles stuck in the face, a take off, showing deep ligature marks.

Can the paramedics keep up? Can Medical supplies keep up? Questions are being asked all over Wuhan.

The lettering on those suits is crooked

Wuhan Jihe Hospital medical staff back

Piho won't forget the late night of January 28th. At the intersection of Wuhan and Caidian District Highway, he and Bao Qiangui were going to pick up the first medical supplies from Fosun to the front line from Shanghai.

On the evening of January 26, Fosun mobilized global forces to procure 10,000 masks to arrive in Shanghai. After more than 20 hours, they will be transported to the front through the Shanghai-wuhan 900 km freight lifeline. And every day after that, it will never stop.

It was a windy and rainy night and the temperature was just over zero degrees. The rain made a jarring noise against the car window. According to the requirements of the two ambulances parked at the monitoring station, on foot rushed to the service area waiting for two Shanghai plates, up to 17.5 meters long red box-type truck.

The first car missed the intersection, Pihao quickly drove, chasing dozens of kilometers back.

It was freezing rain and the roads were closed. "Like Wuhan's air is full of viruses" , Pihao flashed out the idea.

Then he saw Baoqingui in the rain with a cell phone call for an hour, to guide the car over, but also to communicate the driver's protection. At about 2 am, the two containers were finally unloaded at the Jihe Hospital. The truck was disinfected and immediately returned to Shanghai.

Jihe hospital is divided into two areas. Zone 1-3 is in the "clean" West Wing, and zone 4-8 is in the "polluted" East Wing, which is also the isolation ward for new pneumonia patients. Boxes of materials were moved into the West floor warehouse, because storage space is not enough, many piled up in the outpatient hall.

At 5 pm on January 31, Wu Qiong, the 40-year-old director of the Sensory Department of Yueyang's Guangji Hospital, arrived at the hospital and happened to see Fosun's supply vehicles parked in front of the hospital. A warm current rushed up from his stomach. "It's just a feeling of peace, " he said, grinning. The main responsibility of hospital sense department is to prevent cross infection of patients and medical staff.

Tao Fei, the ICU expert of Foshan Chancheng Central Hospital, went to Jihe hospital first thing is to investigate the material building. He was born in the Department of critical care most concerned about high-flow oxygen therapy equipment, which is the treatment of severe new coronary pneumonia patients indicator equipment, hospital in the province many urgent. When told that there are 20 sets, Shanghai procurement over, just in place, "immediately know the bottom of my heart. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Foshan Zen medicine ICU director Tao Fei (second right) and the medical team of two other experts for patient consultation

Abundance can sometimes be a "sweet" burden. Tao Fei received every day are the highest standard of protective clothing, and not the same style, some pants edge with the Zodiac, some underworld or red road. He knew English, Japanese, French, and some of the letters on the labels were too crooked to read.

The difference is that some zippers are so high that they can get stuck up to the neck; others require self adhesive to seal in between Zippers; and still others are so airtight that they cover the entire face, exposing only the eyes. "There's a hat and a mask under the suit. It's like wearing three layers of clothing on a hot day. "

He later asked to know that this is Fosun in the first time from more than 20 countries in the world's rapid procurement of medical-grade protective clothing. The squiggly letters could be Hindi or Portuguese, corresponding to where they were purchased.

Three of my patients have been discharged

Fosun medical elite to join, the core goal of only one: through early treatment, so that patients do not develop serious illness. New Coronaviruses are tricky because they can cause the disease to suddenly deteriorate after a period of relative stability, "holding the nodes is crucial, " Tao explained.

Targeted training is necessary. Jia Xiaomin arrived in the first few days of the hospital, the main focus is to let the hospital to fill the smoking section of the basic knowledge as quickly as possible. Every night, he dissected the methods of diagnosing and treating new coronary pneumonia one by one from respiratory infection, the basic manifestations of pneumonia, how to identify on the image, how to check blood items, how to do blood item analysis, etc. , defining oxygen partial pressure and oxygen saturation is a key concern for most of the medical staff drawn from other departments to have a focus.

Tao Fei in the treatment of patients, the most important work is to comb the case, the development of critical patients in the hospital history. ICU has a famous saying: There is no sudden change of illness, only the change of illness was suddenly found. Whether to find the symptom of disease in time or not determines whether a fresh life will turn to serious disease or go home for Reunion, which is also the value of Jihe hospital as a diagnosis and treatment hub.

Fosun Medical anti-epidemic Expert Group leader Professor Jia Xiaomin in rounds, and encourage patients

Yang Yong, a medical team leader from Shenzhen's Hang Seng Hospital in Wuhan, had a typical case. On the first day, the patient's sats were normal. By the time of rounds the next day, his fingers were all purple, and only 80 percent of them were Oxygenation, a red flag. After treatment with a high-flow oxygen machine, the patient improved.

"every point in the progression from early stage to critical illness must be controlled, " says Tao, explaining that the Oxygenation data is one of the points at which timely oxygen therapy can reduce a patient's chance of developing a critical illness. The mortality rate of severe cases is very high. As of February 15, there were 8,530 severe cases in Wuhan, with a case fatality rate of 2.96% , which is higher than that in Hubei and the whole country.

One of the patients in his ward got better after oxygen therapy. But the airflow through the nasal cavity, bring bad proprioception. "The patient is repeated repeatedly, do not cooperate, transfer to superior hospital to intubate finally. " Tao Fei both deplore and unwilling.

How to get the patients to cooperate, how to comfort the patients, this is also a big problem for the hospital.

It's normal for patients to be anxious when they're in isolation. One patient was admitted because of abdominal pain and nucleic acid test positive. He has been emotional, do not understand how the stomach pain received here in the hospital, suspected a misdiagnosis, asked again nucleic acid testing, also do not cooperate with treatment, every day just repeated the test results. The medical staff had to patiently explain the clinical manifestations of the new coronary pneumonia and persuade him to treat it with peace of mind. Three days later, he saw the word "positive" in his face lost, after a long silence, said a "Go! Wuhan Go! China go! "

Ji He hospital's head nurse Wu Jiao summed up the experience, as a medical staff, first of all to actively disseminate knowledge to patients, as far as possible to eliminate their inner fear, just said "don't be afraid" of the word useless.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital head nurse Wu Jiao in the isolation ward

And one of the patients told her she was in the hospital with her family around. Now this illness, the family can not accompany, can only regard the nurse as the family member. "We talk to them, they will feel very relieved, feel much better, more willing to treat" , Wu Jiao introduced his method.

Patient Comfort is also a manpower challenge. Since the day of the "city closure" , the four head nurses of Jihe Hospital have worked 29 days in a row, refusing to get off the line of fire.

Wu Jiao, from the rehabilitation department, was transferred to the infected area for the first time. "The workload has multiplied. ". Because many patients have difficulty breathing, she spends a lot of time with instruments other than intravenous fluids and other routine work. Breathing Machine, nebulizer, central oxygen supply system, high-flow hygroscopic therapeutic apparatus, etc, are in uninterrupted use, must ensure the stability of the patient's vital signs.

Compared with common pneumonia, new coronary pneumonia is highly infectious, which requires special attention to prevent cross-infection in the ward. The nurses work every day, spraying disinfectant, every other day to the patient to change the bed linen cover, unified to the designated place cleaning and disinfection. These jobs used to be shared by caregivers, but many of them were cut off by traffic and now have to be handled by health care workers themselves.

The arrival of medical professionals like Tao Fei and Wu Qiong has greatly relieved the pressure on the hospital itself. The hospital staff would joke that seeing people arrive was like seeing a cookie.

We're getting more men. A few days ago, the head of the Jihe Hospital, Liu Zaikui, asked the hospital to force shifts, requiring medical staff to take shifts. At present, the ratio of medical care / patient is about 1:3 in Jihe hospital, with about 36 patients in one ward and 12 doctors and nurses on shift, the treatment is gradually entering the normal stage.

The patient also slowly steady state of mind, more understanding of the medical staff is not easy. For example, when you're talking to a doctor, you keep your distance. When you cough, do not approach. Many initially impatient patients, learned that the aid team is from Jiangsu, Guangdong's specialist elite, they raised their fists high, to make encouraging gestures.

Each mask "human flesh" express delivery to more than 80 hospitals

12 days ago, Piho's ambulance broke down. On the way back from the airport to the hospital, the clutch of the ambulance full of medical protective equipment burned out.

From January 29, the first batch of Fosun procurement materials arrived in Wuhan, Chen Yuqing and Bao Qingui one of the focus of work is to solve the problem of effective distribution of materials in Hubei Province.

Every day, the two receive hundreds of phone calls and thousands of wechat messages from Epidemic Prevention Headquarters at all levels, major hospitals, provincial medical teams in Hubei Province, and even hospital department directors, all hoping for emergency assistance with protective materials.

No one thought, Wuhan and Hubei's medical supplies shortage, is a continuing problem. On January 31, the eighth day of the closure, the Government of the People's Republic of China held a press conference, specifically responding to the question, "the Red Cross has received a large number of materials, why are hospitals still short of materials? " .

Put the life-saving medical protection materials to the sun can not reach, the government temporarily out of place, can only point-to-point "human meat" express delivery. The car has to be used frequently because emergency is life-saving.

But with so much demand, how can supplies be efficiently distributed? Command has established that waste is an inefficient donation, that every mask must be used to its best advantage, and that every life-threatening item must be delivered precisely.

On behalf of Fosun and Jihe Hospital, 1000 sets of medical-grade protective clothing were delivered to the Wuhan Union Hospital (Wuhan Union Hospital) by Bao Qingui, Fosun's vice-commander in Wuhan and CEO of Fosun Medical

Chen Yuqing and baoqingui adopted the most earthy method -- a telephone call. Each day, the two spent more than 14 hours staring at their phones, keeping in close contact with people on the ground, verifying the true status of each hospital, and tracking their changing roles during the war.

Hard data are how many quarantined wards are set up in a hospital, and how many health care workers work in quarantined wards and fever clinics. If a hospital does not have an isolation ward, but only a fever clinic, then medical-grade protective clothing with sealant tape and N95 masks in the red zone are not covered.

Of course, we must also analyze the situation in the affected areas. The situation in Xiaogan and Huanggang is the most serious among the prefectural-level cities under Hubei's jurisdiction because they are close to Wuhan and their medical resources are not particularly abundant. Xiangyang, Yichang and Jingzhou are among the worst-hit areas, with at least a few large triple-a hospitals.

From the other side in the communication attitude, can also judge the degree of shortage of protective materials. "For example, if it's really urgent, he will pick it up as soon as I call him. If I say I'll get a car in two days, it means I'm not so nervous at the moment, " Bao said, analyzing the verbal message.

Wuhan Jihe Hospital
